---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Delete your account — Atlas">
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Delete your Atlas account</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>

      <p>
        You can delete your Atlas account at any time. This page explains how
        to request deletion, what data is removed, and what (if anything) we
        keep afterwards.
      </p>

      <h2>How to delete your account</h2>

      <h3>In the app (fastest)</h3>
      <p>
        Open Atlas, then go to <em>Settings &rarr; Delete account</em>. Confirm
        the action when prompted. Your account and personal data are scheduled
        for deletion immediately and removed within seven days.
      </p>

      <h3>By email (if you can't access the app)</h3>
      <p>
        Email
        <a href="mailto:aris@myatlas.fit?subject=Delete%20my%20Atlas%20account">aris@myatlas.fit</a>
        from the email address registered on your account, with the subject
        <em>&ldquo;Delete my Atlas account&rdquo;</em>. We verify the request
        against the registered address and complete the deletion within seven
        days. We may ask one follow-up question to confirm identity if the
        request looks ambiguous.
      </p>

      <h2>What gets deleted</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Profile</strong> — name, email, phone number, password hash, units, training goal, profile picture.</li>
        <li><strong>Workouts</strong> — every workout you've logged: sets, reps, weights, durations, notes.</li>
        <li><strong>Programs and templates</strong> — programs you built or were assigned, including any custom exercises you added.</li>
        <li><strong>Challenges</strong> — challenges you opted into and your progress on them.</li>
        <li><strong>Gym memberships</strong> — your membership records at any gyms or studios you've joined.</li>
        <li><strong>Push notification tokens</strong> — device tokens used to deliver notifications.</li>
        <li><strong>Crash reports</strong> — anonymised reports linked to your account ID are scrubbed within 90 days of deletion (Sentry's standard retention).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we keep, and why</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Encrypted backups</strong> — for up to 30 days after deletion,
          your data may still exist in encrypted database backups used for
          disaster recovery. These backups are not accessible during normal
          operation and are automatically purged on rotation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Server logs</strong> — request timestamps, IP addresses, and
          user-agent strings are retained for 30 days for security and abuse
          prevention. They contain no fitness or profile data.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Aggregate, anonymised metrics</strong> — counts (total
          workouts logged, total active users) that no longer reference your
          identity may be retained indefinitely.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Timeline</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Within seconds</strong> — your account is signed out and login is disabled.</li>
        <li><strong>Within seven days</strong> — your personal data is removed from production systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Within thirty days</strong> — encrypted backups containing your data are rotated out and purged.</li>
        <li><strong>Within ninety days</strong> — crash reports referencing your account ID are purged by Sentry's automatic retention.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Sub-processors</h2>
      <p>
        Deletion requests propagate to all sub-processors listed in our
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>: Render (database), Cloudflare R2
        (uploaded media), Resend (email logs), Firebase Cloud Messaging (push
        tokens), and Sentry (crash reports). Marketing pixels (Meta, TikTok)
        run on the landing page only and have no link to your in-app account.
      </p>

      <h2>Other rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK GDPR / EU GDPR you can also request a copy of your data,
        correct anything inaccurate, or restrict processing without deleting
        the account. Email
        <a href="mailto:aris@myatlas.fit">aris@myatlas.fit</a> from the address
        on your account. We respond within thirty days. Full details are in
        our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about deletion or your data:
        <a href="mailto:aris@myatlas.fit">aris@myatlas.fit</a>.
      </p>

      <a href="/" class="back-link">Back to home</a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding: 80px 0;
    min-height: 60vh;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--navy-700);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy-700);
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  h3 {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--navy-700);
    margin-top: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .updated {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--light-text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  p, ul {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--light-text-secondary);
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  a { color: var(--coral-600); }
  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
